Great with boots and a thick sweater for fall.The skirts are slightly different in length but sit over the knee.
All 3 have slight imperfections as they are vintage but over all in very good shape.

name: Double Zip Alpaca Cowl by Emiline
description: Double Zip Alpaca Cowl by Emiline - Designed in chicago and handknit in south america this soft cowl has many different faces. It can be a cowl, a scarf, a hood and a skirt. It has a metal zipper that can be zipped open from either side. It has no top or bottom.

name: Double Gauze Sweater by Butapano
description: Double Gauze Sweater by Butapano - 100% wool soft and stretchy this beautiful sweater is both warm and stunning. Richly textured, two layers of a gauzy knit intertwine across the entiresweater. Snug fit pull over a wonderful winter piece.

description: Urban Rambler Wrap skirt - These Hmong wrap skirts are 44 inches wide and approx 30 inches long. They are embroided all over in shades of rich reds, and earthy brown. Heavy pleated hemp fabric wrap fully around you and keep you warm. Great fall/winter skirt.
